    "created_at": "2016-05-24T05:59:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-24T07:37:02Z",
    "body": "When running in electron, navigator.language is \"en-GB\" while in the desktop version of Chrome on the same device it's set to \"sv\".\n\nAlso, I added an event listener for keydown to the document, and both electron and Chrome are reporting the same; keyCode=190 for dot and keyCode=188 for comma. It's just that the comma sign doesn't appear in the input field in electron while it does in Chrome.\n"
