    "created_at": "2016-05-25T05:18:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-25T05:18:19Z",
    "body": "I just tried to run a modified version of [helloworld](https://github.com/hokein/electron-sample-apps/tree/master/helloworld) with electron v1.1.1 with the same result: `navigator.language` is \"en-GB\", and comma sign doesn't work in input fields with type \"number\". \n\nHere's the modified index.html if anyone's interested:\n\n```\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n    <body>\n        <input type=\"number\" />\n        <script type=\"text/javascript\">\n           alert(navigator.language);\n        </script>\n    </body>\n</html>\n\n```\n"
  },
